The paper discusses the relationship between citation numbers and perceived impact of scientific publications, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category, as the paper deals with the opinions of experts in their respective fields. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also relevant, as the paper discusses the use of citation data to assess scientific impact. cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) are less likely but still possible categories, as the paper touches on the biases and preferences of researchers in their own work.
